Governor of Katsina State, Aminu Bello Masari yesterday told Nigerian Army to subdue and completely eliminate the bandits terrorising the state and neighbouring Zamfara, Kaduna and Niger states. The governor spoke  in Katsina  Chamber, when he received a delegation of top military officers led by the Chief of Army Staff, Lt Gen Tukur Buratai, ahead of Army Day celebration in the state. According to Governor Masari, the bandits only understand killings and raping, hence military force is the only option to get rid of them completely. He urged the Chief of Army Staff to use this opportunity to subdue them completely, adding that the bandits only professed Islam but do not practice the religion. The governor, therefore maintained that government would not give any opportunity to the enemies of the state in whatsoever disguise to continue to terrorise and cause harm to innocent citizens of the state. He promised to support the military in terms of equipment and hard wares to effectively tackle the bandits once and for all. He also called on the residents of the areas concern to also support the security personnel with reliable information.